2185 /// A pure virtual base class for all recipes modeling header phis, including
2186 /// phis for first order recurrences, pointer inductions and reductions. The
2187 /// start value is the first operand of the recipe and the incoming value from
2188 /// the backedge is the second operand.
2189 ///
2190 /// Inductions are modeled using the following sub-classes:
2191 ///  * VPCanonicalIVPHIRecipe: Canonical scalar induction of the vector loop,
2192 ///    starting at a specified value (zero for the main vector loop, the resume
2193 ///    value for the epilogue vector loop) and stepping by 1. The induction
2194 ///    controls exiting of the vector loop by comparing against the vector trip
2195 ///    count. Produces a single scalar PHI for the induction value per
2196 ///    iteration.
2197 ///  * VPWidenIntOrFpInductionRecipe: Generates vector values for integer and
2198 ///    floating point inductions with arbitrary start and step values. Produces
2199 ///    a vector PHI per-part.
2200 ///  * VPDerivedIVRecipe: Converts the canonical IV value to the corresponding
2201 ///    value of an IV with different start and step values. Produces a single
2202 ///    scalar value per iteration
